    • Method Detail

      • checkCurrentTileMovableObject

        private void checkCurrentTileMovableObject​(GameObject object)
        this method check if the given GameObject is a Player object, if so calls the checkCurrentTilePlayer method. if not calls the gameOver function.
        Parameters:
        object - the Object to be checked

      • checkCurrentTilePlayer

        private void checkCurrentTilePlayer​(Player player)
        checks if the tile where the player is at currently contains another object. if the other object is a planet sets it to visited. if meteorite or spacePirate calls the gameOver method with boolean false if wormhole calls the gameOver method with boolean true
        Parameters:
        player - the spaceship in the galaxy

      • gameOver

        public void gameOver​(java.lang.Boolean win)
        this method is called when the Game is over. it has different functions for a Winning Case of Losing Case. if Win = true it sets a HighScore if Win = false return immediately to the Menu
        Parameters:
        win - this tells the method if a player has won or lost

      • populateGalaxy

        protected void populateGalaxy​(Galaxy galaxy)
                       throws java.io.IOException
        this method populates the Galaxy, before calling this method the galaxy contains only empty tiles. this method creates an arrayList filled with all possible coordinates for this grid. then it gives each object Planet,PlayerMeteoriteWormhole a Coordinate object and removes it from the arrayList. And gives this object to the Galaxy class, which sets it in the right Tile
        Parameters:
        galaxy - it uses a Galaxy object to check the number of coordinates it should create.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an input or output operation is failed
